    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> halloumi</strong> widthways into 4 <span class=\"text-danger\">[8]</span> equal-sized strips</p><p>Then slice each strip in half so you are left with 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16] </span><strong>halloumi sticks</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi sticks</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden</p>",
